 for multiple jurisdictions (e.g., GDPR, HIPAA, California consumer law, general commercial). For each jurisdiction, include test contracts that meet requirements and contracts with known compliance gaps (missing data retention policies, inadequate liability clauses, etc.). Verify the checker identifies whether all requirements are met and provides reasoning for any gaps (e.g., 'missing GDPR data retention policy'). Confirm the final report contains the compliance determination with supporting evidence for all jurisdictions tested.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Understanding jurisdiction-specific compliance requires real LLM reasoning; mocks cannot reliably simulate nuanced regulatory interpretation.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When two reviewers flag the same clause with conflicting assessments (e.g., extractor says 'standard' but risk assessor says 'high risk'), the merge step preserves both assessments with attribution.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is pure merge logic, not LLM capability. The failure mode is algorithmic: merge logic incorrectly selects one assessment and discards the other, loses attribution information, or corrupts the output format. These failures can be caught at Integration level by testing the merge function with realistic mocked inputs that deliberately conflict. No LLM capability testing is needed; the merge function combines structured outputs from the reviewers.","test_description":"Create mocked outputs from all three reviewers where they explicitly disagree on the same clause. Example: clause extraction says 'standard payment term (30 days),' risk assessor flags the same clause as 'high risk' due to late payment penalties, compliance checker says 'acceptable under jurisdiction X.' Run merge and verify the final report contains all three assessments with unambiguous attribution (e.g., '[Risk Assessor] high risk because: late payment penalties exceed...'). Test multiple conflict scenarios: all three disagreeing, two agreeing against one, etc. Verify no assessment is lost and no attribution is scrambled or ambiguous.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Merge logic is testable at Integration with realistic mocked inputs; no LLM dependency required.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — dispatching to all three reviewers, collecting results, merging into a unified report — completes correctly for a real contract without losing any individual reviewer's findings.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a full agentic pipeline with multiple steps (dispatch clause extractor, dispatch risk assessor, dispatch compliance checker, merge results). The failure boundary is 'findings are lost during orchestration' or 'concurrent execution doesn't collect all results.' While orchestration logic could be tested at System level with mocked LLMs, realistic testing of a full pipeline requires Workflow level: verifying all three agentic reviewers execute correctly, all findings from each are collected before merge, timeouts are handled, and no data is lost across the pipeline.","test_description":"Execute the full pipeline end-to-end on realistic legal contracts of varying complexity. Verify all three reviewers are dispatched concurrently and complete within configured timeout. Confirm that all results from each reviewer are collected (no partial results or dropped findings). Verify the merge step receives complete input from all three reviewers and produces a unified report containing all clause extractions, all risk flags, and all compliance determinations. Test with contracts of different sizes and complexity to ensure pipeline integrity scales. Include error scenarios: one reviewer times out, one reviewer returns a malformed response, partial failures. Verify the system either gracefully degradates (partial report with available findings) or retries/handles errors without losing already-collected findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Testing a full agentic pipeline requires Workflow-level thinking to verify orchestration, concurrency, and multi-step coordination work end-to-end with realistic findings.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.4}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12688,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12688},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2191b094-ad30-4e52-b0ed-f8ec89980080","uuid":"3fd5197f-8764-40ba-b037-bd882f73a710"}
